{"_type":"issue","id":"ModelTagger2-8pf","title":"Recursive --zips: tag + upload must handle nested folders","description":"Both tag and upload assume model archives sit directly in --zips, so a nested\nincoming library is mostly missed.\n\n- tag: src/tagging.py uses Path(zips_dir).iterdir() (non-recursive) — archives\n  in subfolders are never tagged.\n- upload: src/manyfold_ingest.py uses source = Path(zips_dir) / filename (flat),\n  and the CSV stores only path.name (basename), so nested sources aren't found\n  and same-basename files in different subfolders collide on one CSV row.\n\nFix: tag recurses with rglob and writes the path RELATIVE to --zips as the CSV\nfilename (recursive + collision-free); upload joins that relative path onto\n--zips to locate the source. match_model and _model_dir_name already use\nPath(...).stem/.name (final component), so naming/matching keep working with a\nrelative-path filename. Add tests for nested discovery, relative-path CSV, and\ncollision avoidance.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Tim Broder","owner":"timothy.broder@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-18T20:50:46Z","created_by":"Tim Broder","updated_at":"2026-06-19T01:31:23Z","started_at":"2026-06-19T01:27:57Z","closed_at":"2026-06-19T01:31:23Z","close_reason":"Fixed in PR #41: tag recurses with rglob and writes relative-path CSV filenames; upload re-joins onto --zips","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
