{"_type":"issue","id":"ModelTagger2-c64","title":"_model_dir_name doesn't dedupe repeated words, producing doubled model titles","description":"Vendor 'doubled name' filenames (e.g. 'Sister Superior_Sister+Superior.zip') produce a doubled model title/folder when staged into Manyfold: _model_dir_name (src/manyfold_ingest.py:98) yields 'Sister Superior Sister Superior', which becomes both the staged folder name and the datapackage.json title/name. Surfaced in Manyfold as a model titled/slugged 'sister-superior-sister-superior'. normalize_name already dedupes repeated words via filter_query_tokens (so match_model works), but _model_dir_name only does regex cleanup with no dedupe, so the human-facing title/folder is doubled.\n\nFix: dedupe repeated words case-insensitively in _model_dir_name (preserving order and original casing, mirroring filter_query_tokens' seen-set), without dropping digits/apostrophes that the title legitimately needs.\n\nAdd a test for the doubled-name -\u003e single-title case (e.g. 'Sister Superior_Sister+Superior.zip' -\u003e 'Sister Superior'), and confirm normal/non-doubled names are unaffected.\n\nNote: this is distinct from the Manyfold 'Path does not match template' problems, which are Manyfold's path-template/Organize-files feature reacting to our flat staged folder vs a tag-nested template -- not a bug in our upload.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Tim Broder","owner":"timothy.broder@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-19T11:25:11Z","created_by":"Tim Broder","updated_at":"2026-06-19T11:38:57Z","started_at":"2026-06-19T11:36:39Z","closed_at":"2026-06-19T11:38:57Z","close_reason":"Fixed: _model_dir_name dedupes repeated words case-insensitively (combined PR)","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"ModelTagger2-0vk","title":"Add tagged_at timestamp column to tagging CSV","description":"Record when each file was tagged. Append a tagged_at column (ISO-8601 UTC) to the tagging CSV header and write the current time for each newly-tagged/retried row. Kept rows on resume retain their original timestamp. Resume logic must migrate older CSVs that predate the column by backfilling an empty timestamp instead of forcing a fresh file. Upload reads via DictReader so the extra column is ignored.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"Tim Broder","owner":"timothy.broder@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-19T10:58:24Z","created_by":"Tim Broder","updated_at":"2026-06-19T11:02:52Z","started_at":"2026-06-19T10:58:28Z","closed_at":"2026-06-19T11:02:52Z","close_reason":"Implemented in PR #42: trailing tagged_at ISO-8601 UTC column with in-place migration of pre-timestamp CSVs","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
