{"_type":"issue","id":"ModelTagger2-bwz","title":"Log retrieval distance + weak-context flag to tagging.log for diagnosability","description":"When a file gets sparse tags (e.g. a blank faction), we currently can't tell from the logs WHY — we have to infer it from token counts and the slug math. Aveline.stl came back with no faction while 'Aveline Plasma no Shield.stl' did, and the only available explanation was inferred (single-token query -\u003e likely unfiltered fallback past the 0.8 weak-context threshold -\u003e model told to ignore lore -\u003e declined faction), not recorded.\n\nMake this diagnosable instead of inferred: in run_tagging (src/tagging.py), include per-file retrieval diagnostics in the tagging.log 'Tagged ...' line (and/or skip lines), specifically:\n- best-match distance (distances[0])\n- whether the retrieval was slug-filtered vs unfiltered fallback (slug_filtered)\n- whether the weak-context note fired (the _WEAK_CONTEXT_DISTANCE guard on the unfiltered path)\n\nSo a future 'why did X get no faction?' is answerable straight from tagging.log. Small, log-only change; add a test asserting the new fields appear (the weak-context-fired case is already exercised by test_structured.py).","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"Tim Broder","owner":"timothy.broder@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-06-19T11:34:18Z","created_by":"Tim Broder","updated_at":"2026-06-19T11:38:58Z","started_at":"2026-06-19T11:36:40Z","closed_at":"2026-06-19T11:38:58Z","close_reason":"Implemented: tagging.log Tagged line now records dist/slug_filtered/weak_context (combined PR)","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
